; RoomNameTable / UIStringTable
;
; 95-entry × 10-byte text table. DrawSprite (#R31634) reads 10 bytes starting
; at (#R28221 + N×10) and renders them as a 10-character label by blitting the
; CharBitmaps (#R26869) glyph for each byte — i.e. the ASCII text *is* the
; "sprite data". Indices 0–46 are #R28221 (room / item / deck names); indices
; 47–94 are #R28691 (UI / menu / action labels).
;
; Entries 57–60 embed the four cursor-arrow UDG codes ($8A–$8D) inside the
; otherwise-ASCII text.
