; CrewStateTable
;
; 6 × 8-byte crew records (initial values for 6 active crew + 1 partial slot
; for the alien). Per-record layout (read via IX-indexed accesses in the
; per-frame routines):
;     +0 = action timer countdown
;     +1 = crew ID (low 6 bits) | direction flag (bit 6) | flags
;     +2 = current corridor position (0..18)
;     +3 = action state (0=dead/none, 1=idle, 2=move, 3=wait, 5=investigate,
;                       6=move-long, 7=attack)
;     +4 = unused / pad
;     +5 = pixel X coordinate
;     +6 = pixel Y coordinate
;     +7 = alive flag (0 = dead, non-zero = alive)
@label=CrewStateTable
b29573 DEFB 0,64,12,0,0,2,2,2  ; crew 0
