; RoomDispatchTable
;
; 34 × 16-bit function pointers for the per-room game handler dispatch.
; Indexed as table[room_mode × 2] where room_mode is the byte at #R31252.
; Dispatched via JP (HL) from #R35314 (RoomModeDispatch). Pairs of
; entries often share the same handler.
;
; Room mode → handler:
;    0-1  RoomModeDispatch (#R35314)   — self-call entry, restarts loop
;    2-3  RoomHandler_2    (#R35338)   — corridor-edge handler
;    4    RoomHandler_4    (#R35578)   — corridor positioning
;    5    RoomHandlerNop   (#R35448)   — no-op (returns)
;    6-12 RoomHandlerCommon(#R35163)   — standard corridor room
;    13   RoomHandler_13   (#R35222)   — special corridor 13 logic
;    14-16 RoomHandlerNop  (#R35448)
;    17-19 RoomHandler_17  (#R35210)   — alt corridor-position handler
;    20-23 RoomHandlerNop  (#R35448)
;    24   RoomHandler_24   (#R35560)   — sets crew action state = 2
;    25-29 RoomHandler_25  (#R35382)   — multi-step room state
;    30-31 RoomHandlerNop  (#R35448)
;    32   RoomHandlerNop2  (#R35449)   — second no-op variant
;    33   RoomHandler_33   (#R35451)   — terminal room handler
;
; Bytes past the 34-entry table (at #R33862) form the RoomDispatchTailExtra
; — likely an overflow continuation if room_mode is ever > 33.
;
@label=RoomDispatchTable
w33794 DEFW 35314,35314,35338,35338
 33802 DEFW 35578,35448,35163,35163
 33810 DEFW 35163,35163,35163,35163
 33818 DEFW 35163,35222,35448,35448
 33826 DEFW 35448,35210,35210,35210
 33834 DEFW 35448,35448,35448,35448
 33842 DEFW 35560,35382,35382,35382
 33850 DEFW 35382,35382,35448,35449
 33858 DEFW 35451,35638

; Data block at #R33862
;
; Previously misclassified as a code routine ("GetCorridorTableEntry"). This
; range is actually three back-to-back data tables used by the rest of the
; game:
;
;   #R33862..#R33875 (14 bytes, 7 × 16-bit pointers) — likely the tail of
;       the RoomDispatchTable at #R33794 (extra entries for modes >33, all
;       sharing the small handler pool used by RoomDispatchTable).
;   #R33876..#R33891 (16 bytes, 8 × 16-bit pointers) — CrewActionDispatch,
;       indexed by crew/alien action state in (IX+3). Action 0 returns
;       early; actions 1-7 jump to the matching handler. Used by the
;       routine at #R36014.
;   #R33892..#R34635 (744 bytes) — MessageTextTable, 34 strings terminated
;       by byte 255. Substitution codes inside the strings: 254 = actor
;       name, 253 = target name, 252 = room name, 145 = apostrophe glyph.
;       Walked and rendered by the routine at #R37221.
;
@ignoreua
@label=RoomDispatchTailExtra
b33862 DEFW 35725,35448,35787,35845  ; 7 × 16-bit pointers (room-handler tail)
 33870 DEFW 38398,38398,35440
