; CrewHitsAlien — alien-side combat handler. Called from
; CrewAction4_Handler (#R37547) when the actor in state 4 has (IX+1)
; matching $737F (the alien's identity from CommonGameInit, #R42451).
;
; This routine is dual-purpose: it both enqueues the "{actor} hits the
; ALIEN" dialogue AND houses the **alien's direct kill primitive** at
; #R37733, fired when the alien's corridor scan position is 12.
;
; Guards: re-asserts that (IX+1) matches the alien identity, then
; requires pixel coords IX+4 >= 2 and IX+6 >= 2 (sprite fully placed).
; Calls #R44986 to clear the scan-slot, then #R31823 to locate the
; alien's corridor scan position into (31248):
;
;   (31248) == 17       → silent: JP to ClearActionState
;   (31248) >= 20       → silent (template sentinels)
;   (31248) == 16       → "net" outcome: write $FF to $7376 (slot 0
;                         byte +0) to disable the alien, then enqueue
;                         message #3 "{actor} nets the ALIEN"
;   else                → "hit" outcome at #R37646: enqueue message #4
;                         "{actor} hits the ALIEN", then dispatch on
;                         the saved (31248):
;                           - {0..5, 18, 19}: INC alien's wound counter
;                             at $73B2 (byte +4 of slot 0). If it
;                             reaches the Auto_83D1 threshold, JP 44125
;                             (alien-defeated path).
;                           - {6, 7}: enqueue msg #5 "Tracker is broken"
;                           - {8..11}: decrement Auto_83D2 entry for
;                             this corridor cell; on underflow enqueue
;                             msg #6 "extinguisher empty".
;                           - **== 12: the alien's kill primitive at
;                             #R37733**. Calls #R37876 to gather up to
;                             three candidate slots (Auto_839F +
;                             NearestCrewA/B) sharing the alien's
;                             sprite class. For each: clear their
;                             entries in the 22-byte anim table at
;                             $7504, then if their slot's byte +7 is
;                             still zero stamp it to 1 (killed) and
;                             clear their byte +4 wound counter. Then
;                             alien's wound counter += 5 (cost of
;                             attack); if it crosses Auto_83D1 → JP
;                             44125. Otherwise CALL 31417 (rebuild
;                             corridor view) and JP 37992 (Auto_9468).
;                           - {13..15}: JP 37831 — decrement Auto_83D2
;                             entry, then either msg #7 or JP 41022.
;
; In short: when the alien enters combat at corridor cell 12 (the
; alien-spawn anim slot, value 32 in the CommonInit_AnimTable
; template), the routine kills the alien's three sprite-class
; "encounter slots" outright by stamping byte +7 = 1 on each. That is
; the alien's direct attack — it doesn't decrement wound counters
; like the Android does in CrewAction7_Handler; it kills in one tick.
;
; This routine parallels #R40941 (CrewHitsAndroid) in structure but
; refers to the alien (slot 0 at $7376) and emits messages #3 / #4
; instead of #31 / #32.
@label=CrewHitsAlien
*37584 LD A,(29567)  ; A = alien-slot identity byte
 37587 CP (IX+1)     ; re-check: IX is the alien slot
 37590 RET NZ        ; defensive: not the alien → bail
 37591 LD A,(IX+4)   ; A = pixel X-tile
 37594 CP 2          ;
 37596 RET C         ; X-tile < 2 → alien not fully on screen, bail
 37597 LD A,(IX+6)   ; A = pixel Y
 37600 CP 2          ;
 37602 RET C         ; Y < 2 → bail
 37603 CALL 44986    ; clear (31248) scan slot, A = CrewIndex
 37606 CALL 31823    ; populate (31248)/(31249) with corridor positions
 37609 LD A,(31248)  ; A = alien's corridor scan position
 37612 CP 17         ;
 37614 JP Z,37555    ; pos 17 → silent
 37617 CP 20         ;
 37619 JP NC,37555   ; pos >= 20 → silent (sentinel cells)
 37622 CP 16         ;
 37624 JR NZ,37646   ; pos != 16 → "hits the ALIEN" branch
 37626 LD HL,29566   ; HL = $7376 (alien slot byte 0)
 37629 LD (HL),255   ; mark alien slot as "netted/inactive"
 37631 CALL 37924    ;
