; DrawShipMap
@ignoreua
;
; Draws the Nostromo ship overview map and handles game-mode selection.
; Sets border green, fills attributes (32), clears display, then blits the
; deck plan as tile blocks at fixed screen positions. After drawing, prints
; the crew names via #R31690 (one name per corridor segment) and the
; four-line menu ("1: Short Game", "2: Long Game", "3: Introduction",
; "4: Select") from the text table at #R43141 (#R43141).
@ignoreua
;
; Key input loop reads port $F7FE:
;   Key 1 — highlight "Short Game"   (selection 0)
;   Key 2 — highlight "Long Game"    (selection 1)
;   Key 3 — highlight "Introduction" (selection 2)
;   Key 4 — confirm: dispatch through 3-word table at #R43135 (#R43135)
;            to the handler for the highlighted mode, then return
;
; "4: Select" is a confirm key, not a fourth game mode.
;
; Used by the routine at #R36457.
